10 (e) If a county election board determines that:
11 (1) a ballot provided by an electronic voting system:
12 (A) must be corrected as provided by IC 3-11-2-16 because of
13 the omission of a candidate, political party, or public question
14 from the ballot; or
15 (B) is an absentee ballot that a voter is entitled to recast under
16 IC 3-11.5-4-2 because the absentee ballot includes a candidate
17 for election to office who:
18 (i) ceased to be a candidate; and
19 (ii) has been succeeded by a candidate selected under
20 IC 3-13-1 or IC 3-13-2; and
21 (2) machines used in the test conducted under this section did not
22 contain a ballot that was reprinted or corrected to remove the
23 omission of a candidate, political party, or public question, or
24 indicate the name of the successor candidate;
25 the county election board shall conduct an additional public test
26 described in subsection (b) using the machines previously tested and
27 containing the reprinted or corrected ballots.
28 SECTION 21. IC 3-12-1-1, AS AMENDED BY P.L.64-2014,
29 SECTION 68, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
30 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 1. Subject to sections 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 9.5, and 13 of
31 this chapter, the primary factor to be considered in determining a
32 voter's choice on a ballot is the intent of the voter. If the voter's intent
33 can be determined on the ballot or on part of the ballot, the vote shall
34 be counted for the affected candidate or candidates or on the public
35 question. However, if it is impossible to determine a voter's choice of
36 candidates on a part of a ballot or vote on a public question, then the
37 voter's vote concerning those candidates or public questions may not
38 be counted.
39 SECTION 22. IC 3-12-1-5, AS AMENDED BY P.L.195-2025,
40 SECTION 14, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
41 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5. (a) This subsection does not apply to a ballot
42 card voting system or an electronic voting system. Except as provided
2026 IN 1133—LS 6304/DI 149

25
1 in subsection (d), A voting mark made by a voter on or in a voting
2 square at the left of a candidate's name or political party's name shall
3 be counted as a vote for the candidate. or candidates of the political
4 party.
5 (b) This subsection applies to a ballot card voting system. A voting
6 mark made by a voter:
7 (1) on or in a circle, oval, or square; or
8 (2) to connect a connectable arrow;
9 immediately below or beside a candidate's name or political party's
10 name shall be counted as a vote for the candidate. or candidates of the
11 political party, except as provided in subsection (d).
12 (c) This subsection applies to a direct record electronic voting
13 system. A voting mark made by a voter touching a touch sensitive point
14 or button below or beside a candidate's name or political party's name
15 shall be counted as a vote for the candidate. or candidates of the
16 political party, except as provided in subsection (d).
17 (d) A voter who wishes to cast a ballot for a candidate for election
18 to a school board office or an at-large district to which more than one
19 (1) person may be elected on a:
20 (1) county council;
21 (2) city common council;
22 (3) town council; or
23 (4) township board;
24 must make a voting mark for each individual candidate for whom the
25 voter wishes to cast a vote. A straight ticket voting mark on a paper
26 ballot, ballot card voting system, or electronic voting system shall not
27 be counted as a straight party ticket voting mark as a vote for any
28 candidate for an office described by this subsection.
29 SECTION 23. IC 3-12-1-7, AS AMENDED BY P.L.21-2016,
30 SECTION 23, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
31 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 7. (a) This subsection applies whenever a voter:
32 (1) votes a straight party ticket; and
33 (2) votes only for one (1) or more individual candidates who are
34 all of the same political party as the straight ticket vote.
35 Except as provided in subsection (d) or (e), the straight ticket vote shall
36 be counted and the individual candidate votes may not be counted.
37 (b) This subsection applies whenever:
38 (1) a voter has voted a straight party ticket for the candidates of
39 one (1) political party;
40 (2) only one (1) person may be elected to an office; and
41 (3) the voter has voted for one (1) individual candidate for the
42 office described in subdivision (2) who is:
2026 IN 1133—LS 6304/DI 149

26
1 (A) a candidate of a political party other than the party for
2 which the voter voted a straight ticket; or
3 (B) an independent candidate or declared write-in candidate
4 for the office.
5 If the voter has voted for one (1) individual candidate for the office
6 described in subdivision (2), the individual candidate vote for that
7 office shall be counted, the straight party ticket vote for that office may
8 not be counted, and the straight party ticket votes for other offices on
9 the ballot shall be counted.
10 (c) This subsection applies whenever:
11 (1) a voter has voted a straight party ticket for the candidates of
12 one (1) political party; and
13 (2) the voter has voted for more individual candidates for the
14 office than the number of persons to be elected to that office.
15 The individual candidate votes for that office may not be counted, the
16 straight party ticket vote for that office may not be counted, and the
17 straight party ticket votes for other offices on the ballot shall be
18 counted.
19 (d) This subsection applies whenever:
20 (1) a voter has voted a straight party ticket for the candidates of
21 one (1) political party;
22 (2) more than one (1) person may be elected to an office; and
23 (3) the voter has voted for individual candidates for the office
24 described in subdivision (2) who are:
25 (A) independent candidates or declared write-in candidates;
26 (B) candidates of a political party other than the political party
27 for which the voter cast a straight party ticket under
28 subdivision (1); or
29 (C) a combination of candidates described in clauses (A) and
30 (B).
31 The individual votes cast by the voter for the office for the independent
32 candidates, declared write-in candidates, and the candidates of a
33 political party other than the political party for which the voter cast a
34 straight party ticket shall be counted unless the total number of these
35 individual votes is greater than the number of persons to be elected to
36 the office. The straight party ticket votes for the office shall not be
37 counted. The straight party ticket votes for other offices on the voter's
38 ballot shall be counted.
39 (e) This subsection applies whenever:
40 (1) a voter has voted a straight party ticket for the candidates of
41 one (1) political party;
42 (2) more than one (1) person may be elected to an office; and
2026 IN 1133—LS 6304/DI 149

27
1 (3) the voter has voted for individual candidates for the office
2 described in subdivision (2) who are:
3 (A) independent candidates, declared write-in candidates, or
4 candidates of a political party other than the political party for
5 which the voter cast a straight party ticket under subdivision
6 (1); and
7 (B) candidates of the same political party for which the voter
8 cast a straight party ticket under subdivision (1).
9 The individual votes cast by the voter for the office for the independent
10 candidates, the declared write-in candidates, and the candidates of a
11 political party other than the political party for which the voter cast a
12 straight party ticket, and the candidates of the political party for which
13 the voter cast a straight party ticket shall be counted unless the total
14 number of these individual votes is greater than the number of persons
15 to be elected to the office. The straight party ticket votes for the office
16 shall not be counted. The straight party ticket votes for other offices on
17 the voter's ballot shall be counted.
18 (f) If a voter votes a straight party ticket for more than one (1)
19 political party, the whole ballot is void with regard to all candidates
20 nominated by a political party, declared write-in candidates, or
21 candidates designated as independent candidates on the ballot.
22 However, the voter's vote for a school board candidate or on a public
23 question shall be counted if otherwise valid under this chapter.
24 (g) (a) If a voter does not vote a straight party ticket and the number
25 of votes cast by that a voter for the candidates for an office are less
26 than or equal to the number of openings for that office, the individual
27 candidates votes shall be counted.
28 (h) (b) If a voter does not vote a straight party ticket and the number
29 of votes cast by that a voter for an office exceeds the number of
30 openings for that office, none of the votes concerning that office may
31 be counted.
32 SECTION 24. IC 3-12-1-7.1 IS REPEALED [EFFECTIVE JULY
33 1, 2026]. Sec. 7.1. Notwithstanding section 7 of this chapter, a straight
34 party vote does not count for any candidate for a school board office.
35 SECTION 25. IC 3-12-1-7.5, AS AMENDED BY P.L.21-2016,
36 SECTION 24, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
37 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 7.5. (a) If a voter votes for one (1) individual
38 candidate for an office for which only one (1) person may be elected
39 and also writes in the name of another candidate for the same office,
40 neither vote may be counted.
41 (b) If a voter votes for at least one (1) individual candidate for an
42 office for which at least two (2) people may be elected and also writes
2026 IN 1133—LS 6304/DI 149

28
1 in the name of at least one (1) candidate, the vote for that office may
2 not be counted unless the number of individual votes cast for the office,
3 when added to the number of write-in votes cast for that office, is less
4 than or equal to the number of seats available for that office.
5 (c) If a voter votes an individual or a straight party vote for a
6 candidate for an office and also writes in the name of the same
7 candidate for the same office, only one (1) vote for that candidate may
8 be counted.
9 SECTION 26. IC 3-12-1-8 IS REPEALED [EFFECTIVE JULY 1,
10 2026]. Sec. 8. (a) Except as provided in subsection (b), a voting mark
11 made by a voter on or in a circle containing a political party device
12 shall be counted as a vote for each candidate of that political party on
